ttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fpakistan-elections-live-updates-both-nawaz-sharif-imran-khan-declare-victory-poll-body-silent-5029110%5C%22%3EPakistan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftaiwan-ruling-partys-lai-ching-te-who-rejects-chinas-territorial-claims-wins-presidential-election-news-agency-reuters-4855975%5C%22%3ETaiwan%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fvladimir-putin-wins-russia-presidential-polls-with-88-votes-1st-official-results-5258125%5C%22%3ERussia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%20And%20some%20have%20thrown%20up%20surprises%20-%20who%20would%20have%20thought%20that%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20members%20of%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Imran%20Khan's%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20party%2C%20who%20fought%20as%20independents%20(after%20a%20military%20crackdown%20on%20the%20party)%2C%20would%2C%20defying%20all%20odds%2C%20win%20more%20seats%20than%20the%20Pakistan%20People's%20Party%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIncumbents%20Trip%20Up%20In%20South%20Korea%2C%20Turkey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20unexpected%20result%20was%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20South%20Korean%20National%20Assembly%20elections%20this%20week%2C%20where%20the%20liberal%20opposition%20won%20a%20landslide%20majority%20to%20retain%20its%20control%20of%20parliament.%20The%20Democratic%20Party%20(DPK)%20and%20smaller%20opposition%20parties%20jointly%20won%20192%20of%20300%20seats%2C%20much%20to%20the%20chagrin%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fsouth-koreas-liberal-opposition-wins-landslide-parliamentary-vote-5416482%5C%22%3EPresident%20Yoon%20Suk%20Yeol%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20results%20are%20widely%20seen%20as%20a%20midterm%20referendum%20on%20President%20Yoon%2C%20who%20still%20has%20three%20years%20left%20in%20office.%20Yoon's%20People%20Power%20Party%20(PPP)%20had%20been%20struggling%20to%20achieve%20its%20agenda%20in%20a%20legislature%20dominated%20by%20the%20DPK.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Turkey%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fturkeys-opposition-knocks-tayyip-erdogan-in-key-local-elections-5348253%5C%22%3EPresident%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan's%3C%2Fa%3E%20ruling%20Justice%20and%20Development%20Party%20(AKP)%20suffered%20its%20%26quot%3Bmost%20severe%26quot%3B%20election%20setback%20this%20week%2C%20the%20worst%20since%20Erdogan%20came%20to%20power%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20all%20accounts.%20In%20the%20nationwide%20local%20elections%2C%20the%20opposition%20Republican%20People's%20Party%20(CHP)%20won%2035%20out%20of%2081%20municipalities%2C%20including%20mayoral%20victories%20in%20Istanbul%2C%20Ankara%2C%20Izmir%2C%20Bursa%2C%20and%20Antalya.%20This%20is%20its%20best%20showing%20since%20Turkey's%201977%20general%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomy%2C%20Inflation%20Are%20Key%20Threats%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20tripped%20up%20leaders%20like%20Yoon%20and%20Erdogan%20and%20their%20parties%3F%20In%20both%20cases%2C%20the%20economy%20and%20inflation%20were%20major%20factors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Yoon's%20case%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20unfavorable%20results%20for%20the%20ruling%20party%20indicate%20that%20the%20rising%20prices%20of%20essential%20vegetables%20for%20family%20sustenance%2C%20coupled%20with%20the%20opposition's%20critique%20of%20the%20administration's%20perceived%20shortcomings%20in%20welfare%2C%20had%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20the%20electorate's%20mindset%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20a%20post-poll%20analysis%20by%20the%20Washington-based%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%20(CSIS).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Cem%3EGuardian%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20had%20said%20just%20before%20the%20South%20Korean%20National%20Assembly%20polls%20on%20April%2010%20that%20the%20prices%20of%20green%20onions%20had%20sky-rocketed%2C%20turning%20it%20from%20a%20%26quot%3Bsimple%20staple%20of%20Korean%20cooking%20to%20a%20powerful%20symbol%20of%20voter%20anger%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20Asia's%20fourth-largest%20economy.%20The%20price%20of%20apples%20increased%20by%20nearly%2090%25%2C%20marking%20the%20largest%20one-year%20jump%20since%201980%2C%20the%20report%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDon't%20Write%20Erdogan%20Off%20Just%20Yet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20Turkey%2C%20the%20mismanagement%20of%20the%20economy%20with%20stifling%20inflation%20were%20the%20major%20reasons%20for%20the%20poor%20showing%20by%20Erdogan's%20party%20by%20all%20accounts.%20%26quot%3BSunday's%20%5BApril%207%5D%20local%20races%20highlighted%20growing%20public%20discontent%20with%20the%20ruling%20AKP.%20Many%20CHP%20supporters%20touted%20years%20of%20high%20inflation%20for%20their%20turn%20against%20Erdogan.%20Official%20figures%20estimate%20that%20inflation%20hit%20nearly%2070%25%20in%20February%2C%20though%20unofficial%20numbers%20predict%20the%20figure%20to%20be%20closer%20to%2010%25%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20%3Cem%3EForeign%20Policy%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0in%20its%20commentary%20on%20the%20Turkish%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20poll%20results%20are%20being%20seen%20as%20putting%20a%20question%20mark%20on%20Erdogan's%20future.%20For%20one%2C%20they%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20a%20setback%20to%20his%20efforts%20to%20adopt%20a%20new%20constitution%20that%20could%20extend%20his%20rule%20beyond%202028%2C%20when%20his%20term%20is%20set%20to%20expire.%20Then%20there%20are%20those%20who%20wonder%20whether%20Erdogan%20will%20stick%20to%20his%20recent%20suggestion%20that%20the%202023%20election%2C%20in%20which%20he%20garnered%2052%25%20of%20the%20vote%2C%20would%20be%20his%20last.%20But%20the%20one%20thing%20you%20can%20be%20sure%20of%20is%20Erdogan's%20capacity%20to%20spring%20a%20surprise.%20He%20has%20been%20in%20power%20in%20Turkey%20since%202003%20and%20has%20weathered%20many%20a%20storm%2C%20including%20widespread%20opposition%20protests%20and%20a%20coup%20attempt.%20Given%20all%20this%2C%20it's%20wise%20not%20to%20write%20Erdogan%20off%20just%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThings%20Go%20South%20For%20Sunak%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20economy%20was%20a%20major%20and%20common%20reason%20for%20the%20bad%20showing%20in%20polls%20by%20the%20parties%20of%20incumbents%20in%20South%20Korea%20and%20Turkey%2C%20some%20other%20factors%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20economy%20could%20explain%20the%20dire%20predictions%20being%20made%20about%20the%20polls%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20has%20to%20call%20in%20the%20UK%20before%20January%202025.%20In%20February%2C%20Reuters%20reported%20that%20falling%20inflation%2C%20the%20prospect%20of%20interest%20rate%20cuts%20and%20signs%20that%20Britain's%20economy%20was%20gathering%20some%20pace%20after%20recession%20had%20sounded%20like%20an%20electoral%20godsend%20for%20the%20struggling%20Sunak.%20But%20it%20also%20added%20that%20none%20of%20this%20may%20translate%20into%20good%20news%20for%20his%20Conservative%20Party.%20Recently%2C%20an%20opinion%20poll%20predicted%20that%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20is%20hurtling%20towards%20its%20heaviest%20election%20defeat%20since%201977.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Conservatives%20have%20been%20in%20power%20for%2014%20years%20by%20itself%20or%20as%20part%20of%20a%20coalition.%20It's%20a%20long%20time%20by%20any%20standards.%20But%20anti-incumbency%20alone%20cannot%20explain%20the%20unpopularity%20of%20the%20Conservatives.%20There%20was%20Brexit%2C%20which%20wreaked%20havoc%20on%20the%20UK%20economy%2C%20piling%20costs%20on%20the%20country's%20businesses%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20economic%20growth.%20Brexit%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20reason%20for%20Britain's%20particularly%20high%20inflation-a%20recent%20study%20by%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20found%20that%20Brexit%20was%20responsible%20for%20about%20a%20third%20of%20UK%20food%20price%20inflation%20since%202019%2C%20adding%20nearly%20%26amp%3B%23163%3B7%20billion%20(%248.8%20billion)%20to%20Britain's%20grocery%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20was%20the%20controversy%20over%20PM%20Boris%20Johnson's%20partying%20amid%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%20Johnson's%20successor%20Liz%20Truss%20resigned%20within%2045%20days%20in%20office%20after%20after%20her%20controversial%20economic%20policies%20caused%20the%20pound%20to%20crash%20and%20interest%20rates%20to%20rise%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20days.%20Her%20successor%2C%20Sunak%2C%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20steady%20hand%2C%20but%20things%20haven't%20quite%20worked%20according%20to%20plan%20-%20largely%20because%20the%20economy%20hasn't%20done%20as%20well.%20Even%20as%20people%20across%20the%20UK%20are%20still%20to%20recover%20from%20the%20pandemic-induced%20economic%20pain%2C%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20has%20already%20pushed%20up%20energy%20prices%2C%20further%20straining%20household%20budgets.%20There%20are%20also%20major%20rumblings%20within%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20to%20replace%20Sunak.%20All%20in%20all%2C%20he%20is%20struggling%2C%20against%20a%20number%20of%20odds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiden's%20Faulty%20Messaging%20Can%20Benefit%20Trump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcross%20the%20Atlantic%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20a%20picture%20of%20good%20health%20compared%20to%20many%20Western%20countries.%20%26quot%3BThe%20US%20economy%20grew%20faster%20than%20previously%20estimated%20in%20the%20fourth%20quarter%2C%20boosted%20by%20strong%20consumer%20spending%20and%20business%20investment%20in%20nonresidential%20structures%20like%20factories%20and%20healthcare%20facilities%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20%3Cem%3EReuters%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20at%20the%20end%20of%20March.%20A%20Commerce%20Department%20statement%20said%20profits%20were%20rising%20at%20a%20solid%20clip%20driven%20by%20nonfinancial%20corporations.%20Inflation%20was%20cooling%20and%20joblessness%20was%20at%20a%20record%20low%20-%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20dipped%20from%203.9%25%20to%203.8%25%20and%20has%20now%20remained%20below%204%25%20for%2026%20straight%20months%2C%20the%20longest%20such%20streak%20since%20the%201960s%2C%20an%20%3Cem%3EAP%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20all%20this%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20trailing%20behind%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20opinion%20polls%20and%20surveys.%20The%20prime%20reason%20for%20this%20seems%20to%20be%20that%20the%20good%20news%20from%20the%20economic%20space%20has%20not%20been%20packaged%20well%20for%20voters.%20There%20seems%20to%20be%20a%20clear%20mismanagement%20of%20the%20political%20messaging%20to%20the%20voters.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20Biden's%20re-election%20bid%20is%20dependent%20heavily%20on%20the%20swing%20states%20-%20Pennsylvania%2C%20Michigan%2C%20Nevada%2C%20Arizona%2C%20Georgia%20and%20North%20Carolina.%20While%20Trump%20leads%20Biden%20in%20all%20these%20states%2C%20the%20two%20are%20tied%20in%20Wisconsin.%20In%20all%20seven%20states%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20an%20overwhelming%20issue%20for%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20is%20the%20age%20factor.%20Biden%20is%2081%2C%20and%20voters%20are%20deeply%20concerned%20about%20that%2C%20though%20Trump%20is%20only%20a%20tad%20bit%20better%20on%20this%20count%3B%20he%20will%20be%2078%20in%20June.%20Other%20uncertainties%20plague%20Trump%20legally.%20He%20is%20the%20first%20ex-president%20in%20US%20history%20to%20be%20criminally%20charged%20across%20faces%20four%20separate%20cases.%20Then%20there%20are%20several%20civil%20cases%20relating%20to%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20his%20business%20empire.%20And%20there%20are%20legal%20appeals%20to%20be%20settled%20too%2C%20including%20one%20on%20whether%20he%20is%20immune%20from%20prosecution.%20All%20in%20all%2C%20a%20complicated%20picture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20still%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go%20for%20the%20November%20polls.%20Will%20the%20Biden%20camp%20be%20able%20to%20devise%20a%20strong%20campaign%20to%20drive%20home%20the%20message%20of%20how%20well%20the%20economy%20is%20today%20after%20the%20mismanagement%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20crisis%20under%20Trump%3F%20That%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat's%20clear%2C%20however%2C%20is%20that%20the%20global%20economic%20headwinds%20have%20hit%20incumbents%20across%20countries%20hard.%20Some%20may%20manage%20to%20pull%20through%20it%3B%20others%20may%20not%20be%20so%20lucky.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Elizabeth%20Roche%20is%20Associate%20Professor%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20International%20Affairs%2C%20OP%20Jindal%20Global%20University%2C%C2%A0Sonipat)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712922180000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F3mpbe1go_sunak-biden_625x300_12_April_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fuks-rishi-sunak-to-us-joe-biden-no-incumbent-has-it-easy-this-year-thanks-to-economy-5426492%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20South%20Korea%20and%20Turkey%20to%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%2C%20incumbent%20heads%20of%20state%20in%20most%20poll-bound%20countries%20are%20struggling%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20power%20and%20popularity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fuks-rishi-sunak-to-us-joe-biden-no-incumbent-has-it-easy-this-year-thanks-to-economy-5426492%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Not%20even%20Ambedkar%20...'%3A%20PM%20takes%20on%20oppn's%20Constitution%20remarks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712921968000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-109248487%2Cimgsize-1100359.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fnot-even-ambedkar-pm-modi-t