anjali-ads-hearing-775212https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fvideo%2Fnews%2Fnews%2Fplease-spare-me-begs-officer-during-supreme-court-patanjali-ads-hearing-775212%5C%22%3EPatanjali%20Ayurved%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20violating%20the%20law.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20significant%20remark%2C%20the%20court%20said%20an%20apology%20given%20to%20it%20could%20not%20be%20taken%20lightly%20as%20there%20was%20a%20larger%20issue%20concerning%20public%20health.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20also%20concerned%20about%20the%20FMCGs%20%5Bfast-moving%20consumer%20goods%20companies%5D%20that%20are%20taking%20consumers%20up%20the%20garden%20path%20and%20making%20people%20buy%20their%20products%2C%20who%20end%20up%20bearing%20adverse%20consequences.%20There%20are%20major%20fault%20lines%20in%20the%20system%20and%20this%20fault%20line%20is%20not%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20your%20company%20but%20the%20health%20of%20the%20public%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%2C%20questioning%20the%20state%20government%20for%20keeping%20its%20eyes%20%26quot%3Bshut%26quot%3B%2C%20took%20strong%20exception%20to%20the%20Uttarakhand%20government's%20apparent%20lack%20of%20action%20regarding%20Patanjali's%20exaggerated%20claims%20about%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20its%20products%20and%20its%20criticism%20of%20modern%20medicine%20during%20the%20peak%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Advertising%20Standards%20Council%20of%20India's%20(ASCI)%20half-yearly%20complaints%20report%20published%20in%20November%20last%20year%2C%20healthcare-related%20ads%20were%20at%20the%20top%20in%20terms%20of%20violating%20the%20law.%20They%20constituted%2021%20per%20cent%20of%20all%20processed%20ads.%20The%20report%20also%20observed%20that%20there%20was%20a%20significant%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20ads%20that%20directly%20went%20against%20the%20Drug%20and%20Magic%20Remedies%20Act%20of%201954.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20The%20Case%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Medical%20Association%20(IMA)%20filed%20a%20petition%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20August%202022%20based%20on%20a%20Patanjali%20advertisement%20published%20in%20several%20newspapers%20in%20July%20the%20same%20year.%20The%20advertisment%2C%20titled%20'Misconceptions%20Spread%20By%20Allopathy%3A%20Save%20Yourself%20And%20The%20Country%20From%20The%20Misconceptions%20Spread%20By%20Pharma%20And%20Medical%20Industry'%2C%20featured%20yoga%20expert%20Ramdev%20calling%20allopathy%20a%20%26quot%3Bstupid%20and%20bankrupt%20science%26quot%3B%20and%20claimed%20that%20allopathic%20medicine%20was%20responsible%20for%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Covid-19-related%20deaths%20in%20the%20country.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2021%2C%202023%2C%20during%20the%20first%20hearing%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20court%20orally%20warned%20Patanjali%20against%20false%20claims%20and%20said%20it%20would%20impose%20a%20fine%20if%20the%20company%20didn't%20stop%20publishing%20misleading%20advertisements.%20Less%20than%20two%20months%20after%20that%2C%20however%2C%20the%20court%20received%20an%20anonymous%20letter%20flagging%20the%20continued%20publication%20of%20false%20and%20misleading%20advertisements%20by%20Patanjali.%20Taking%20cognisance%20of%20it%2C%20the%20court%20issued%20a%20contempt%20notice%20to%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%20and%20its%20MD%20for%20flouting%20its%20orders.%20The%20SC%20also%20panned%20the%20Central%20government%20for%20not%20restraining%20the%20company.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20the%20court%2C%20upon%20not%20having%20received%20a%20reply%20to%20the%20contempt%20notice%2C%20passed%20an%20order%20seeking%20the%20personal%20appearance%20of%20Balakrishna%20and%20Ramdev.%20The%20Uttarakhand%20government%20was%20also%20made%20a%20party.%20Both%20Balakrishna%20and%20Ramdev%20issued%20an%20apology%2C%20but%20the%20top%20court%20on%20April%202%20dismissed%20it%20as%20mere%20%26quot%3Blip%20service%26quot%3B%2C%20criticising%20the%20company%20for%20failing%20to%20file%20proper%20affidavits%20and%20giving%20it%20a%20week%20to%20do%20so.%20On%20April%2010%2C%20however%2C%20the%20court%20ultimately%20rejected%20Patanjali's%20apologies%20over%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20were%20first%20sent%20to%20the%20media.%20%26quot%3BTill%20the%20matter%20reached%20the%20court%2C%20the%20contemnors%20did%20not%20find%20it%20fit%20to%20send%20us%20the%20affidavits.%20They%20sent%20it%20to%20the%20media%20first%2C%20until%207.30%20pm%20yesterday%20it%20was%20not%20uploaded%20for%20us.%20They%20clearly%20believe%20in%20publicity%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPast%20Incidents%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20have%20been%20several%20cases%20involving%20misleading%20advertisements.%20In%20December%202016%2C%20a%20Haridwar%20court%20had%20imposed%20a%20Rs%2011%20lakh%20fine%20on%20Ramdev's%20company%2C%20Patanjali%20Ayurved%20Ltd.%20The%20penalty%20arose%20from%20charges%20of%20misbranding%20and%20misrepresentation%20of%20its%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20April%20of%202023%2C%20a%20huge%20controversy%20erupted%20again%20when%20a%20viral%20video%20revealed%20that%20Bournvita%2C%20produced%20by%20Mondelez%20International%20India%2C%20contained%20dangerously%20high%20amounts%20of%20sugar.%20The%20National%20Commission%20for%20Protection%20of%20Child%20Rights%20(NCPCR)%20issued%20a%20notice%20to%20the%20company%2C%20ordering%20it%20to%20%C2%A0withdraw%20all%20misleading%20advertisements%2C%20packaging%20and%20labels.%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20advertisements%20weren't%20stalled%2C%20but%20the%20brand%20did%20claim%20that%20it%20had%20reduced%20the%20quantity%20of%20sugar%20in%20the%20children's%20drink.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELegal%20Regulation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMisleading%20advertising%20can%20cause%20serious%20harm%20to%20consumers.%20%C2%A0And%20in%20the%20case%20of%20health-related%20products%2C%20such%20ads%20can%20be%20even%20more%20dangerous.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20present%20case%2C%20since%20the%20primary%20business%20is%20in%20the%20medicinal%20healthcare%20sector%2C%20laws%20such%20as%20the%20Drugs%20and%20Magic%20Remedies%20(Objectionable%20Advertisements)%20Act%20of%201954%2C%20the%20Drugs%20and%20Cosmetics%20Rules%2C%201945%2C%20and%20the%20Advertising%20Standards%20Council%20of%20India's%20Regulation%20Code%20and%20Consumer%20Protection%20Act%2C%202019%2C%20apply%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Aditya%20Bharat%20Manubarwala%2C%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20advocate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternet%20and%20the%20emergence%20of%20new%20ways%20to%20advertise%20have%20further%20aggravated%20the%20challenge.%20Regulation%20has%20been%20unable%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20the%20changing%20nature%20of%20marketing.%20Advertisement%20and%20promotional%20material%20can%20reach%20even%20the%20remotest%20corners%20of%20the%20country%20today%20with%20very%20little%20expenditure%2C%20thanks%20to%20smartphones%20and%20social%20media.%20Our%20actions%20in%20real%20life%20are%20defined%20by%20the%20myriad%20advertisements%20and%20promotional%20content%20we%20see%20on%20our%20social%20media.%20Weight%20loss%2C%20fair%20complexion%2C%20healthy%20oil%20for%20healthy%20heart%20products...the%20list%20is%20endless.%20Brands%20paint%20a%20rosy%20picture%2C%20and%20consumers%20take%20it%20as%20gospel%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20brand%20is%20a%20trust.%20A%20trust%20that%20a%20consumer%20reposes%20in%20an%20offering.%20And%20this%20trust%20must%20not%20be%20broken%20or%20even%20attempted%20to%20be%20broken.%20Brand%20ethics%20is%20a%20serious%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Harish%20Bijoor%2C%20founder%20of%20Harish%20Bijoor%20Consults%20Inc.%20%26quot%3BCorporate%20entities%2C%20brands%20and%20their%20bait%2C%20and%20lure%20offerings%20are%20meant%20to%20be%20integrity-oriented%20offerings.%20One%20must%20not%20swerve%20away%20from%20the%20narrow%20and%20tight%20track%20of%20integrity.%20The%20gold%20standard%20globally%20is%20to%20tell%20the%20truth%20and%20plain%20truth.%20No%20exaggeration.%20No%20falsification.%20No%20lure%20that%20is%20a%20lie%20or%20even%20a%20half-truth.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20along%20with%20other%20deterrents%2C%20brands%20should%20also%20be%20made%20to%20issue%20corrective%20advertisements%20so%20as%20to%20alert%20consumers%20about%20their%20wrongful%20claims%20earlier.%20%26quot%3BExisting%20laws%20say%20that%20any%20advertising%20should%20not%20be%20misleading...An%20advertisement%20for%20medicines%20should%20never%20make%20any%20promise%20or%20claims%20of%20curing%20the%20diseases%2C%26quot%3B%20Manubarwala%20says.%20The%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20is%20a%20cohesive%20legal%20framework%20and%20awareness%20and%20active%20self-regulation%20to%20guarantee%20quality%20communication%20between%20brands%20and%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712912460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2019-06%2Fu4krsiqo_ramdev-patanjali--reuters_625x300_12_June_19.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fpatanjali-saga-is-a-reminder-that-india-needs-better-ad-regulation-5425454%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20is%20a%20cohesive%20legal%20framework%20and%20an%20active%20awareness%20and%20self-regulation%20to%20guarantee%20quality%20communication%20between%20brands%20and%20the%20public.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fpatanjali-saga-is-a-reminder-that-india-needs-better-ad-regulation-5425454%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fpatanjali-saga-is-a-reminder-that-india-needs-