n%20ranges.%20By%20controlling%20the%20population%20of%20these%20sheep%20and%20goats%2C%20the%20snow%20leopard%20gives%20the%20grasses%20and%20plants%20a%20chance%20to%20regenerate%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Namgail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20issue%20the%20feline%20helps%20tackle%20is%20floods.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20prevalence%20of%20natural%20disasters%20in%20the%20region%20is%20compounded%20by%20climate%20change.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20days%20we%20are%20receiving%20more%20rain%20and%20less%20snow.%20As%20the%20rainwater%20flows%20down%20the%20slopes%2C%20the%20loose%20soil%20also%20goes%20with%20it.%E2%80%9D%20Mind%20you%2C%20the%20soil%20is%20loosened%20by%20the%20grazing%20activity%20of%20the%20goats.%20The%20muddy%20water%20floods%20the%20villages%20destroying%20property%20in%20the%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNow%20do%20you%20see%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F86991%2Fovercome-age-old-prejudices-snow-leopard-conservation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20ecological%20linkage%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%E2%80%9D%20Namgail%20asks%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20then%20moves%20on%20to%20explore%20the%20third%20benefit%20of%20having%20the%20animal%20in%20the%20region%20%E2%80%94%20enhancing%20carnivore%20diversity.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20snow%20leopard%E2%80%99s%20preferred%20prey%20are%20the%20Asiatic%20Ibex%20and%20the%20Himalayan%20Blue%20Sheep.%20Preying%20on%20these%20indirectly%20allows%20other%20species%20of%20sheep%20and%20goats%20to%20thrive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20question%20begs%20to%20be%20asked%3A%20if%20an%20animal%20has%20such%20prime%20ecological%20importance%2C%20why%20is%20it%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20extinction%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EProtecting%20the%20%E2%80%98ghost%20of%20the%20mountains%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20moniker%20has%20been%20bestowed%20on%20the%20feline%20for%20its%20natural%20camouflage.%20No%20one%20can%20sense%20it%20approaching%20until%20it%20finally%20shows%20itself.%20With%20hind%20legs%20that%20enable%20it%20to%20leap%20six%20times%20the%20length%20of%20its%20body%20and%20a%20long%20tail%20that%20provides%20it%20balance%2C%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F28377%2Fendangered-species-snow-leopard-spotted-in-the-kumaon-himalayas%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20snow%20leopard%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20for%20centuries%20assumed%20a%20%E2%80%98king%E2%80%99%20status%20in%20the%20mountains%20of%20Afghanistan%2C%20Bhutan%2C%20China%2C%20India%2C%20and%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20is%20that%20the%20snow%20leopard%E2%80%99s%20status%20was%20assessed%20in%201986%2C%201988%2C%201990%2C%201994%2C%201996%2C%202002%2C%20and%202008.%20In%20each%20case%2C%20it%20was%20classified%20as%20%E2%80%98Endangered%E2%80%99.%20But%20in%202008%20the%20animals%E2%80%99%20status%20was%20changed%20to%20%E2%80%98Vulnerable%E2%80%99%20as%20the%20population%20began%20to%20decline%20less%20rapidly.%20But%20the%20decline%20was%20still%20present%2C%20and%20human-animal%20conflict%20was%20to%20blame.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fsnow-leopard-conservancy-6-1711367766.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Retaliatory%20killings%20of%20the%20snow%20leopard%20used%20to%20be%20very%20common%20in%20Ladakh%20pushing%20the%20animal%20to%20the%20brink%20of%20extinction%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fsnow-leopard-conservancy-6-1711367766.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fsnow-leopard-conservancy-6-1711367766-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20http