w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fbook-hotel-1-1710406948-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fbook-hotel-1-1710406948-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fbook-hotel-1-1710406948-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fbook-hotel-1-1710406948-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-344852%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EBhimabai%20started%20the%20hotel%20as%20a%20means%20to%20spread%20the%20joy%20of%20reading!%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAway%20from%20home%20and%20everything%20she%20loved%2C%20Bhimabai%20found%20herself%20alone%2C%20tending%20to%20a%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20husband%20was%20an%20alcoholic%20who%20spent%20most%20of%20his%20time%20wandering%20around.%20Not%20only%20did%20I%20have%20to%20take%20care%20of%20the%20home%2C%20but%20also%20the%20farms%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20adding%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20my%20daughter%20became%20a%20little%20older%2C%20she%20would%20go%20to%20the%20farms%20with%20me.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20her%20children%20growing%20up%2C%20she%20wanted%20to%20send%20them%20to%20school.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20always%20financially%20weak%2C%20but%20my%20husband%E2%80%99s%20addiction%20made%20things%20worse.%20He%2C%20in%20a%20state%20of%20intoxication%2C%20either%20sold%20off%20his%20land%20or%20gambled%20it%20away%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELeft%20without%20a%20means%20to%20feed%20her%20family%2C%20Bhimabai%20would%20work%20for%20hours%20in%20different%20people%E2%80%99s%20fields%20to%20bring%20food%20to%20the%20table.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20fed%20up%20with%20the%20life%20we%20had.%20My%20son%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F342483%2Fmadhya-pradesh-school-teacher-gopal-bhalwala-renovates-government-school-with-own-savings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egoing%20to%20school%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20had%20picked%20up%20a%20newspaper%20distribution%20job%20to%20help%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPravin%20elaborates%20on%20his%20mother%E2%80%99s%20struggle%20from%20his%20perspective%2C%20%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20relatives%20were%20always%20trying%20to%20have%20their%20way%20with%20her.%20My%20father%20was%20a%20father%20only%20in%20name.%20He%20never%20took%20any%20responsibilities.%20Like%20my%20mother%2C%20I%20had%20a%20zeal%20to%20get%20an%20education.%20I%20got%20a%20job%20at%20a%20newspaper%20distributor%20and%20funded%20my%20education%20myself%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20only%20one%20escape%20from%20the%20challenging%20life%20%E2%80%93%20move%20to%20the%20city.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20like%20a%20beacon%20of%20hope%20for%20us.%20I%20would%20probably%20find%20some%20work%20there%2C%20and%20my%20mother%20would%20be%20away%20from%20her%20relatives.%20So%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20sell%20off%20whatever%20was%20left%20of%20our%20land%20and%20moved%20to%20the%20city%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202008%2C%20the%20family%20moved%20to%20the%20city.%20Pravin%20had%20already%20started%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F34699%2Fjuggernaut-by-chiki-sarkar%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublishing%20company%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20days%20were%20looking%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDue%20to%20some%20personal%20reasons%2C%20I%20had%20to%20shut%20down%20the%20publishing%20company%2C%20and%20we%20had%20a%20stock%20of%20Marathi%20language%20books%20with%20us.%20My%20mother%20and%20sister%20did%20not%20know%20much%20beyond%20farming%2C%20so%20they%20started%20a%20makeshift%20tea%20stall%20to%20meet%20our%20expenses%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENo%20phones%2C%20only%20books!%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202010%2C%20Bhimabai%2C%20along%20with%20her%20daughter%2C%20laid%20the%20foundation%20of%20what%20is%20today%20Ajjichya%20Pustakancha%20Hotel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20family%20moved%2C%20the%20taunts%20and%20harsh%20words%20never%20stopped%20following%20her.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20would%20talk%20about%20how%20the%20women%20of%20the%20house%20should%20not%20wander%20around%20selling%20tea%3B%20she%20should%20take%20care%20of%20the%20house.%20But%20I%20did%20not%20care%20about%20those%20taunts%20anymore%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20children%20and%20I%20slowly%20started%20to%20use%20savings%20to%20expand%20the%20tea%20stall%20and%20make%20it%20an%20eatery.%20What%20I%20noticed%20was%20that%20while%20a%20person%20would%20wait%20for%20their%20food%2C%20they%20would%20always%20be%20buried%20in%20their%20phone%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20would%20not%20converse%20with%20each%20other%20but%20would%20keep%20scrolling%20on%20their%20phone.%20I%20found%20the%20habit%20very%20absurd%20and%20wanted%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20woman%20who%20was%20fond%20of%20reading%20but%20never%20got%20the%20chance%20to%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20reintroduce%20the%20habit%20of%20reading%20to%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBooks%20are%20our%20best%20friends.%20They%20are%20your%20companions%20in%20every%20situation.%20We%20started%20off%20with%20just%2025%20books%20in%20a%20stand%20in%20the%20eatery%20and%20it%20kept%20growing.%20We%20started%20encouraging%20people%20to%20pick%20up%20a%20book%20and%20read%20while%20we%20cook%20their%20meal%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBy%20the%20time%20the%20food%20would%20arrive%20at%20their%20table%2C%20they%20would%20have%20already%20reached%20chapter%20two%20of%20the%20book%2C%E2%80%9D%20she