0story.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHistory%20sprinkled%20with%20a%20dash%20of%20sweetness%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVermicelli%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20India%20was%20marked%20by%20every%20region%20putting%20its%20own%20spin%20on%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F281110%2Fmithai-map-of-india-10-lesser-known-indian-sweets-you-must-try-at-least-once%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20West%2C%20adding%20saffron%20and%20chopped%20nuts%20to%20the%20vermicelli%20is%20a%20common%20practice%20while%20in%20the%20North%2C%20this%20is%20substituted%20with%20%3Cem%3Ekhoya%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20the%20South%2C%20coconut%20milk%20is%20added%20to%20get%20a%20thick%20consistency%20while%20those%20in%20Odisha%20and%20West%20Bengal%20prefer%20adding%20rosewater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20vermicelli%20is%20cooked%20depends%20upon%20the%20festive%20occasion%20too.%20For%20instance%2C%20during%20Raksha%20Bandhan%2C%20some%20people%20prepare%20%3Cem%3Emeethe%20java%3C%2Fem%3E%20(vermicelli%20pudding).%20The%20%E2%80%9Causpicious%E2%80%9D%20short%20noodles%20used%20in%20the%20dish%20are%20a%20version%20of%20the%20thinner%2C%20longer%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F285541%2Fsabja-seed-health-benefits-weight-loss-recipe-indian-food%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebeloved%20summer%20drink%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3Efalooda%3C%2Fem%3E%20features%20thicker%20glutinous%20strands%20of%20vermicelli%20dunked%20into%20a%20syrup%20and%20served%20with%20ice%20cream.%20The%20dessert%20traces%20back%20to%20%3Cem%3Efaloodeh%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20Persian%20cuisine%20where%20the%20vermicelli%20would%20be%20made%20from%20frozen%20cornstarch%2C%20mixed%20with%20rose%20water%2C%20lime%20juice%20and%20pistachios.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20too%2C%20there%20are%20different%20varieties.%20I%20recall%20Eid%20feasts%20with%20friends%2C%20where%20half%20of%20the%20group%20preferred%20the%20flowy%20version%20of%20the%20dessert%20(which%20resembled%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekheer%3C%2Fem%3E%20cooked%20with%20milk)%2C%20and%20the%20other%20half%20would%20argue%20that%20the%20dry%20version%20(vermicelli%20sweet%20made%20by%20frying%20the%20noodles%20in%20ghee%2C%20adding%20syrup%20and%20nuts)%20was%20more%20delicious.%20I%20belonged%20to%20the%20former!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhatever%20your%20preference%20for%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20suffices%20to%20say%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F345644%2Fbest-momo-joints-delhi-recommended-by-foodies-dolma-aunty-majnu-ka-tila-yeti-mood-pema%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20just%20a%20meal%2C%20but%20an%20emotion%20for%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F1527DDMBFuI%3Fsi%3DXndnqmlcKz_Uq1zR%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESo%2C%20here%E2%80%99s%20a%20recipe%20for%20%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20chef%20Sanjeev%20Kapoor%20that%20you%20can%20try%20out%20this%20festive%20season.%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%20(serves%20four)%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E10%20g%20vermicelli%20(%3Cem%3Eseviyan%3C%2Fem%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3%20tbsp%20pure%20ghee%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1%20tsp%20green%20cardamom%20powder%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E1%2F2%20cup%20sugar%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethod%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStep%201%3A%20Heat%20%3Cem%3Eghee%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekadai%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%